The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Gopa Dasgupta, 32, who was riding pillion on a motorcycle, died after being hit by a truck at the Sulekha crossing, in Jadavpur, on Friday afternoon. Husband Atanu, who was driving the motorcycle, was critically injured. He is being treated at AMRI. 

 Birendra Bhagat was critically injured when the motorcycle he was riding was hit by a private bus on route 234 at the AJC Bose Road-Ripon Street crossing on Friday morning. Bhagat, who works as a driver in the wireless branch of the city police, was admitted to National Medical College and Hospital. The bus driver has been arrested.

 Sergeant Partho Bose spotted Prakash Gupta, 60, falling unconscious at Lyons Range, in central Calcutta, on Friday morning. The policeman carried Gupta to the medical unit at Writers Buildings, where he was treated. He regained consciousness after half an hour. Bose later took Gupta to his Beleghata home.

 A 65-year-old woman was injured after being hit by a car on APC Road, in Rajabazar, around 3 pm on Friday. Local residents took her to NRS Medical College and Hospital, where her condition was stated to be critical. The driver fled with the vehicle.

 The three-day national annual general meeting of Round Table India and Ladies Circle India, being held at Taj Bengal, will end on Saturday. On Sunday, Round Table India will commemorate its 50th year by inaugurating a primary school in Rasulpur, Hooghly. 

 To Calcutta Ladies Circle 46 and 93 for installing a tubewell for the inmates of an old-age home




